CHIKUNGUNYA (44): INDIA (GUJARAT)
*********************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 29 Oct 2013
Source: Times of India [edited]
http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/ahmedabad/Chikungunya-cases-on-rise/articleshow/24837768.cms


The health department has recorded an increase in the number of patients with chikungunya [virus infection], which was 113 as of October this year [2013].

In October last year [2012], there were only 14 cases of chikungunya [virus infection].

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Ahmedabad is experiencing a mixed outbreak of chikungunya, dengue, and malaria, all mosquito-transmitted pathogens.

The above report does not mention specific vector control measures, especially elimination of _Aedes_ breeding sites to reduce chikungunya and dengue virus transmission. The report also does not indicate whether these cases have been confirmed by laboratory tests.

There were there were 39 cases in Ahmedabad as of mid-August 2013 (see ProMED-mail archive no. 20130813.1870987). The outbreak has continued on into October 2013, and the report above does not indicate that it has ended.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map showing the location of Gujarat state can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1iSU. - Mod.TY]
